title: Adelaide and Antonine: or, the Emigrants: a tale. [In verse.]
[Reflections on the death of Louis XVI. [In verse.]]

A ballad on the death of Louis the Unfortunate, after the manner of Chevy Chase. A description of the appearance of Marie Antoinette's ghost before the Convention. A sonnet on the French atheistical motto, “Death is an eternal sleep.” And an ode on Greatness
